Johnny Mince (born John Muenzenberger) (July 8, 1912 in Chicago Heights, Illinois – December 23, 1994 in Boca Raton, Florida) was an American swing jazz clarinetist.
Mince played with Joe Haymes from 1929 to 1934, and recorded with Red Norvo and Glenn Miller in 1935.
